Syrian President Bashar al-Assad  on Monday condemned a blast which killed former Lebanese Prime  Minister Rafik Hariri as "horrible terrorist act," the official  SANA news agency reported.
A senior Lebanese official said here  on Sunday that evil hands are behind blasts which have been  destabilizing the country since the assassination of former Prime  Minister Rafik Hariri.
The Lebanese parliament opened  Monday a special session to vote on a no-confidence motion against  the government over the assassination of former prime minister  Rafik Hariri two weeks ago.
